  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Iron overload is well study in Thalassemia patients and it's not only related to blood
      transfusions, since intestinal iron absorption is also increased in those patients. Sickle
      cell patients didn't develope significant clinical symptoms and signs of iron overload in
      spite frequent transfusions. The purpouse of this study is to assess the iron overload in
      Sickle cell anemia and Sickle cell Thalassemia patients using clinical parameters and cardiac
      T2*MRI in order to determine the cardiac and liver iron.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
